    Sample coefficients

    sampleCoefs.Rd

    Sample coefficient values from the normal distribution based on the coefficient and standard error

    sampleCoefs(coefTable, replicates)

    Arguments

    coefTable

    data.table. Table of must have columns "Coefficient" for the name of the coefficient, "Value" for the value of the coefficient and "StdErr" for the standard error of coefficients

    replicates

    number of samples to take.

    Value

    A list with elements:

    "coefSamples"

    Bootstrapped coefficients with replicates rows

    "coefValues"

    Coefficient values taken from populationGrowthTable

    Examples

    cfs <- getCoefs(popGrowthTableJohnsonECCC, "recruitment", "ECCC", "M3")

sampleCoefs(cfs[[1]], 10)
#> $coefSamples
